==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Advisable
<hw>Ad*vis"a*ble</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Proper to be advised or to be done; expedient; prudent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Some judge it <qex>advisable</qex> for a man to account with his
heart every day.</q> <rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Ready to receive advice.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>South.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Expedient; proper; desirable;
befitting.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Advisableness</ent>⟦br⟧
